Officials, including Numsa's Irvin Jim and Satu's Zwelinzima Vavi, at Lanxess Chrome Mine during a sit-in, demanding recognition of their union, the reinstatement of dismissed workers and the suspension of an official accused of sexual harassment. RUSTENBURG – The strike at Lanxess Chrome Mine in Rustenburg has been called off. Workers had staged an underground sit-in for nine days at the mine. READ: Numsa hope Lanxess mine strike will end Over 200 mineworkers have been refusing to come to the surface, until action is taken against alleged sexual harassment and victimisation. At least 13 miners were admitted to hospital during the strike, after refusing to eat.